Parliament, Thursday, 29 August 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Transport will today meet with the Road Traffic Infringement Agency (RTIA) in Pretoria. RTIA will present its annual performance plans to the committee. The meeting is also intended to familiarise the new members of the committee with the operations of RTIA which is the custodian of the recently signed Aarto (Administrative Adjudication Road Traffic Offences) law. The committee will also meet with the Road Traffic Management Corporation (RTMC). Details of the meeting are as follows: Time: 15h00
	Venue: Waterfall Office Park, Midrand. All the meetings of the committee are open to the public including the media. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON TRANSPORT, MR MOSEBENZI ZWANE. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Sibongile Maputi (Mr)
